		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Al-Jazari</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Abū al-'Iz Ibn Ismā'īl ibn al-Razāz al-Jazarī</b> (1136-1206) (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" xml:lang="ar">أَبُو اَلْعِزِ بْنُ إسْماعِيلِ بْنُ الرِّزاز الجزري</span>‎) was an important <a href="/wiki/Arab" title="Arab">Arab</a> <a href="/wiki/Ulema" title="Ulema">scholar</a>, <a href="/wiki/Inventions_in_the_Muslim_world" title="Inventions in the Muslim world" class="mw-redirect">inventor</a>, <a href="/wiki/Timeline_of_Muslim_scientists_and_engineers" title="Timeline of Muslim scientists and engineers" class="mw-redirect">mechanical engineer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Artisan" title="Artisan">craftsman</a>, <a href="/wiki/Islamic_art" title="Islamic art">artist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Islamic_astronomy" title="Islamic astronomy" class="mw-redirect">astronomer</a> from <a href="/wiki/Al-Jazira,_Mesopotamia" title="Al-Jazira, Mesopotamia">Al-Jazira, Mesopotamia</a> who lived during the <a href="/wiki/Islamic_Golden_Age" title="Islamic Golden Age">Islamic Golden Age</a> (<a href="/wiki/Middle_Ages" title="Middle Ages">Middle Ages</a>). He is best known for writing the <i>Kitáb fí ma'rifat al-hiyal al-handasiyya</i> (<i>Book of Knowledge of Ingenious Mechanical Devices</i>) in 1206, where he described fifty mechanical devices along with instructions on how to construct them.</p>
